    {
        "id": "igfa1_npcc_parallel",
        "name": "PARALLEL",
        "role": "striker",
        "info": {
            "flavor": "PREPARED BY: UIB-TERMINALCLICHE<li>RECOVERED FOR: UIB-KATABATIC<li>CLEARENCE REQ: SOLEMN VIGIL<br>I can confirm that mechs belonging to pattern group “Parallel” match the profile of contacts first observed during the Calliope Incident (see report: CALAMITY AXIS). We’re still trying to identify the original developer. Current best guesses are SSC, the Armory, Horizon, or even the Cult of the One, but in my opinion, it can’t be any of them. This tech is years ahead of even the largest corprostates, let alone a bunch of cultists in a garage.",
            "tactics": "The Parallel is a highly mobile striker that can dominate large areas of the battlefield by literally being in two places at once. PHASE ECHO lets them position a surrogate that they can switch places with to avoid incoming damage or make reaction attacks. A Parallel’s main weakness is its fragility; it relies on careful positioning and judicious use of REVERT to avoid high-damage attacks. It can’t stand up to repeated damage, and removing its echoes hampers its mobility."
        },
