    {
        "id": "igfa1_npcc_slinger",
        "name": "SLINGER",
        "role": "controller",
        "info": {
            "flavor": "Slinger-class mechs are a favorite among pilots who value skill over raw firepower. Stable, agile and dependable, Slinger frames don’t need military-grade guns or fancy tech; all they need is someone at the controls who knows when to take the shot that ends the fight. Stepping into battle against a Slinger is a nerve-wracking experience: a quiet duel of resolve, each combatant seeking their perfect moment, the razor-thin window that separates the quick from the dead.",
            "tactics": "Slingers are potent area denial specialists who trade heavily on their Deathmark mechanic. It inflicts these upon a critical hit, so it will benefit allies who can provide LOCK ON. Its attacks ignore armor and deal damage even on a miss, and if it’s inflicted a lot of Deathmarks, it can unleash several at once at the startof its turn, threatening multiple foes in a wide radius.<br>The Slinger’s primary weaknesses are its inability to deal with targets at long range and its reliance on Deathmark to be effective. Players inflicting IMPAIRED or using cover will make marks harder to inflict."
        },
